# ORIG TITLE    Dortmund turn on the style to stun Real Madrid . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Polish international Robert Lewandowski scored four goals as Borussia Dortmund dominated Real Madrid on Wednesday to take a commanding 4-1 lead after the first leg of their Champions League semi-final clash at the Westfalenstadion. Former Manchester United winger Cristiano Ronaldo scored from close range just before the break to give the visitors hope but it wasn’t to be for Madrid, who’ll be hoping to bounce back from this loss when both sides meet again for the second leg at the Bernabeu on April 30. The winners will face Bayern or Barcelona in the final at Wembley Stadium on Saturday 25 May. 
